			<a href="#top"><img src="/images/common/up_arrow.gif" width="54" height="13" vspace="6" border="0"></a> 
			  . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . <br>&nbsp;<br>		
			
			
			<div class="header1">New White Paper Published <a name="paper" id="paper"></a></div>
			<img src="/images/home/thumb_pdf_paper.gif" width="97" height="77" align="left">
			
			A new white paper entitled  "<a href="/files/whitepaper.METAwpJCP.pdf" target="_blank">Java
			Standards: The Mandate for Interoperability and Compatibility</a>"  
			is available on the JCP.org site in pdf format. In this META Group
			Research Whitepaper, the role of the Java Community Process (JCP)
			Program is explored and it illustrates how the JCPit delivers platform independence
			and interoperability to the users of Java technology.<br>
			&nbsp;<br>

			<a href="#top"><img src="/images/common/up_arrow.gif" width="54" height="13" vspace="6" border="0"></a> 
              . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
			  <br>&nbsp;<br>
			
			<div class="header1">The JCP @ Upcoming Industry Events <a name="events"></a></div>
            
			<img src="/images/home/thumb_events1.gif" width="95" height="75" align="left">The JCP is participating at several industry events in the coming months.
			<br>&nbsp;<br>  
			JCP EC Member, <strong>Orange</strong>, will be taking their second ?<strong>Code
			Camp</strong>? event for members
			of its developer programme to Sarasota, Florida 
			(US) 18-20 April (<a href="http://www.eventreg.com/orange_code_camp/reg.html" target="_blank">registration
			info</a>).  
			During the event ? comprising 72 hours of learning, coding, demonstrating
			and building ? Orange will be actively seeking input from developers about
			the shape of MID-P 3.0 and feeding it back to the JCP program. Registration
			is encouraged now as places are limited ($249 including accommodation
			and food for 72 hours).
			<br>
			&nbsp;<br>  

			<strong>TeleManagement World</strong> (TMW), Nice (France), 17-19  May. 
			This conference, organized every year by the Telemanagement Forum (TMF), 
			is the largest conference worldwide dedicated to OSS: <a href="http://www.tmforum.org">http://www.tmforum.org</a>.  
			The quarterly JCP program Executive Committee (EC) meeting and JCP Training 
			session will be collocated with TMW, leading to multiple interactions between 
			both events.
			<br>
			&nbsp;<br>

			<strong>The JavaOne Conference</strong>, San Francisco (US), 27-30 June. This conference, 
			now in its tenth year, is one of the largest gatherings in the world of 
			developers, IT managers, and business professionals who are focused on 
			Java technology: <a href="http://java.sun.com/javaone/sf/">http://java.sun.com/javaone/sf/</a>.  The JCP program will 
			have activities planned during the conference-stay tuned for details.
			<br>
			&nbsp;<br>
			
			<a href="#top"> <img src="/images/common/up_arrow.gif" width="54" height="13" vspace="6" border="0"></a> .
			. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
			. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . <br>
			&nbsp;<br>
			
			            <div class="header1">JCP European Training <a name="training" id="training"></a></div>
			            <img src="/images/home/thumb_training1.gif" width="95" height="75" align="left">
						The European edition of the JCP Training & Communication session will be
						held in a one and a half day format on 19 (half day afternoon session) & 20
						May (full day), following TeleManagement World in Nice, France:
						<br>
						&nbsp;<br>
						
						<strong>Training times:  19 May 13:00 - 17:00 and  20 May  9:00 - 17:00</strong>			<br>
						&nbsp;<br>
						This will be a hands-on, interactive session that includes
						modeling a JSR Expert Group and tips on how to utilize the JCP 2.6 enhancements
						introduced last March to increase the transparency, efficiency and participation
						of JSRs. The JCP Training and Communication Sessions present an unique
						opportunity for future Spec Leads and Expert Group Members to meet with
						members of the PMO and experienced Spec Leads & Experts.
						<br>
						&nbsp;<br>
					The sessions are hosted by the PMO free of charge and are
					open to everyone with interest in the JCP Program. If you wish to attend,
					know someone who would like to attend, or would like some more information
					regarding the Training sessions, please contact Liz Kiener at Liz&#064;jcp.org
					or +1 510 550 4353. Additional information is available here: <a href="/en/press/news/JCPtraining05">JCPtraining05</a>.			<br>
				&nbsp;<br>

			<a href="#top"><img src="/images/common/up_arrow.gif" width="54" height="13" vspace="6" border="0"></a> 
              . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
			  <br>&nbsp;<br>
			  
            
            <div class="header1">Noteworthy JSRs <a name="noteworthy" id="noteworthy"></a></div>
           <img src="/images/home/thumb_spotlight1.gif" width="95" height="75" border="0" align="left" class="header1">
		   There are several new JSRs being developed through the JCP program. You can nominate to 
		   serve on the expert group of these JSRs by clicking on the &quot;Join Expert Group&quot; link on the 
			  JSR detail page urls listed below. You can also request to join the Observer Alias of JCP 2.6 
			  JSRs by emailing the spec lead (listed on the JSR detail page).

              <ul>
				<li><a href="/en/jsr/detail.id=271"><strong>JSR-271</strong></a>, Mobile
				  Information Device Profile 3, is now available for review.
				  This JSR will specify the 3rd generation Mobile Information Device Profile
				  (MID-P), expanding upon the functionality in all areas as well as improving
				  interoperability across devices. The review closes 21 March.</li>
				<li><a href="/en/jsr/detail.id=208"><strong>JSR 208</strong></a> Java Business
				  Integration (JBI), is now available for Public Review; this
			    review closes 4 April.</li>
				<li><a href="/en/jsr/detail.id=106"><strong>JSR 106</strong></a>, XML Digital
				  Encryption APIs, is now available for Community Review, this
				  review closes 4 April.</li>
				<li><a href="/en/jsr/detail.id=113"><strong>JSR 113</strong></a>, Java Speech
				  API 2.0, is available for Public Review. This specification
				  defines a cross-platform interface to support speech recognizers and synthesizers.</li>
				<li><a href="/en/jsr/detail.id=228"><strong>JSR 228</strong></a>, Information
				  Module Profile - Next Generation, has passed Public Review
				  ballot. Final release is planned for April 2005.</li>
				<li><a href="/en/jsr/detail.id=226"><strong>JSR 226</strong></a>, Scalable
				  2D Vector Graphics API for J2ME, has completed its work and
				  published the Final Release of the specification.</li>
              </ul>
                <a href="#top"><img src="/images/common/up_arrow.gif" width="54" height="13" vspace="6" border="0"></a>
